description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join the CAMHS Provider Collaborative as an inpatient case manager, supporting effective patient pathways across Kent and Sussex.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The case manager posts are being transferred from NHSE into the Provider Collaboratives. Case managers play a vital role within Provider Collaboratives, providing credible oversight and facilitator of care for patients in receipt of specialised services. They also support the commissioning function by assisting with the monitoring and reviewing of the quality of provision by observing providers in practice and monitoring and reviewing quality information and local intelligence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Provider Collaborative has a new roles available covering Eating disorders CAMHS Kent and Sussex adolescent inpatient provision. You will be required to oversee one hospital and carry a caseload.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As this is a Kent and Sussex job the base can be negotiable within the footprint. Timely travel across the region is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Nina Marshall&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Provider Collaborative Program Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address nina.marshall@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 07823789802&lt;/p&gt;
